{
  "texts": [
    "As anticipated, all the topics were classified as issues due to the highly polarized nature of the topic discussions.",
    "In addition to that, the issues identified using popular n-grams unveiled both unique issues associated with a single topic as well as the common issues, being the central discussion across multiple topics.",
    "For example, Table 8 shows sample topics and issues identified in the Daily Mail.",
    "While 'global warming' is an issue specific to the topic 'Transition to green transportation solutions', 'cost of living' can be observed as a common issue across multiple topics.",
    "The final component of the pipeline aggregates the information retrieved to generate conceptual graphs that we can visualize to illustrate and explore the relationships between topics, issues, entities, and sentiment."
  ]
}